िमुषितावयम् ।","trans":"\"Charming lady! You see the seashore there, where we crossed the sea that night and slept on the shore.\"","words":[{"d":"वरानने","m":"charming lady"},{"d":"समुद्रस्य","m":"ocean's"},{"d":"एतत्","m":"this"},{"d":"तीर्थम्","m":"shore"},{"d":"दृश्यते","m":"see"},{"d":"सागरम्","m":"ocean"},{"d":"उत्तीर्य","m":"landed"},{"d":"वयम्","m":"we"},{"d":"तांरात्रिम्","m":"that night"},{"d":"यत्र","m":"there"},{"d":"उषिताः","m":"slept"}]},{"v":16,"dev":"एषसेतुर्मयाबद्धस्सागरेसलिलार्णवे तवहेतोर्विशालाक्षिनलसेतुःसुदुष्करः ।","trans":"\"Broad eyed lady! Here is the bridge built on the salty ocean by Nala, which was difficult to construct.\"","words":[{"d":"विशालाक्षि","m":"broad eyed"},{"d":"एषः","m":"here"},{"d":"सागरे","m":"on the ocean"},{"d":"सलिलार्णवे","m":"salt ocean"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"बद्धः","m":"bridge"},{"d":"सुदुष्करः","m":"very difficult"},{"d":"नलसेतुः","m":"built by Nala (called Nalasethu as it was built by Nala)"}]},{"v":17,"dev":"पश्यसागरमक्षोभ्यंवैदेहिवरुणालयम् अपारमभिगर्जन्तंशङ्खशुक्तिसमाकुलम् ।","trans":"\"Vaidehi! See the abode of Varuna, impenetrable and immeasurable roaring aloud filled with conches and oystershells.\"","words":[{"d":"वैदेहि","m":"Vaidehi"},{"d":"अक्षोभ्यम्","m":"imperturbable"},{"d":"वरुणालयम्","m":"abode of Varuna"},{"d":"अपारमिव","m":"immeasurable"},{"d":"अभिगर्जन्तम्","m":"roaring aloud"},{"d":"शङ्खशुक्तिसमाकुलम्","m":"hoarding conches, oystershells"},{"d":"सागरम्","m":"ocean"},{"d":"पश्य","m":"see"}]},{"v":18,"dev":"हिरण्यनाभंशैलेन्द्रंकाञ्चनंपश्यमैथिलि विश्रमार्थंहनुमतोभित्त्वासागरमुत्थितम् ।","trans":"\"Mythili! See the mountain which has golden caves and has risen cleaving the ocean in order to give place for Hanuman to rest while crossing the ocean.\"","words":[{"d":"मैथिलि","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"हनुमतः","m":"Hanumantha"},{"d":"विश्रमार्थम्","m":"in order to rest"},{"d":"सागरम्","m":"ocean"},{"d":"भित्त्वा","m":"cleaving"},{"d":"उत्थितम्","m":"risen up"},{"d":"काञ्चनम्","m":"golden"},{"d":"हिरण्यन